[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":649},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F15\u002Fforced-to-eat-mango-frontend-03-mongodb-crud-create\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F15\u002Fforced-to-eat-mango-frontend-03-mongodb-crud-create\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F15\u002Fforced-to-eat-mango-frontend-03-mongodb-crud-create\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F15\u002Fforced-to-eat-mango-frontend-03-mongodb-crud-create\u002F":624,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F15\u002Fforced-to-eat-mango-frontend-03-mongodb-crud-create\u002F":633},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20220215\u002F1747232197\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":605,"date":606,"description":607,"extension":608,"lang":609,"meta":610,"navigation":611,"path":612,"readingMinutes":613,"seo":614,"standalone":615,"stem":616,"tags":617,"tldr":621,"updated":606,"url":622,"__hash__":623},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Fforced-to-eat-mango-frontend-03-mongodb-crud-create.md","Forced to Eat Mango (3): MongoDB CRUD — the Create Part","1003294307",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":600},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,63,75,104,108,111,114,126,132,135,154,161,168,181,186,197,207,215,224,231,290,293,299,346,352,500,507,513,584,587,593,596],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Now that we've gotten comfortable with the common MongoDB Basic operations, the next obvious step is CRUD. So yeah, we're still going to be living in the terminal for this one.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"mongodb-crud","MongoDB CRUD",[17,25,26],{},"Let's talk about CRUD. It's a super common acronym at this point, but let me still spell out what each letter actually means:",[28,29,30,39,47,55],"ul",{},[31,32,33,34],"li",{},"C = Create\n",[28,35,36],{},[31,37,38],{},"Add, build, or create something new",[31,40,41,42],{},"R = Read\n",[28,43,44],{},[31,45,46],{},"Read or query",[31,48,49,50],{},"U = Update\n",[28,51,52],{},[31,53,54],{},"Update",[31,56,57,58],{},"D = Delete\n",[28,59,60],{},[31,61,62],{},"Delete",[17,64,65,66,70,71,74],{},"Before you read on, I'd suggest hopping back into the MongoDB shell and typing ",[67,68,69],"code",{},"use example",", because everything from here on out is CRUD practice inside ",[67,72,73],{},"example",". In case you forgot how to get in, here's the flow one more time:",[76,77,82],"pre",{"className":78,"code":79,"language":80,"meta":81,"style":81},"language-cmd shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","mongo\nuse example\ndb \u002F\u002F make sure we're operating under exampleDB\n","cmd","",[67,83,84,92,98],{"__ignoreMap":81},[85,86,89],"span",{"class":87,"line":88},"line",1,[85,90,91],{},"mongo\n",[85,93,95],{"class":87,"line":94},2,[85,96,97],{},"use example\n",[85,99,101],{"class":87,"line":100},3,[85,102,103],{},"db \u002F\u002F make sure we're operating under exampleDB\n",[12,105,107],{"id":106},"create","Create",[17,109,110],{},"So C stands for Create, and Create means adding\u002Fbuilding\u002Fcreating new stuff. But the syntax we actually use is called Insertion.",[17,112,113],{},"MongoDB gives you two ways to add data:",[28,115,116,121],{},[31,117,118],{},[67,119,120],{},"db.collection.insertOne()",[31,122,123],{},[67,124,125],{},"db.collection.insertMany()",[17,127,128,131],{},[67,129,130],{},"insertOne"," is pretty self-explanatory — it adds one single record.",[17,133,134],{},"Earlier I mentioned that a collection is roughly the equivalent of a Table in SQL. So if the data we want to add today is a user, then we'd write it like this:",[76,136,140],{"className":137,"code":138,"language":139,"meta":81,"style":81},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","db.users.insertOne()\n","js",[67,141,142],{"__ignoreMap":81},[85,143,144,148,151],{"class":87,"line":88},[85,145,147],{"class":146},"sMAXC","db.users.",[85,149,130],{"class":150},"sj_SG",[85,152,153],{"class":146},"()\n",[17,155,156,157,160],{},"So... why do we write it that way? Let me draw a diagram to make the MongoDB structure click. First, let's look at the basic ",[67,158,159],{},"db"," structure:",[17,162,163],{},[164,165],"img",{"alt":166,"src":167},"db structure","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-01-22%2022.23.57.png",[17,169,170,171,173,174,176,177,180],{},"When you type ",[67,172,159],{},", it just shows you which database you're currently in, so the opening move is always ",[67,175,159],{},". The second piece is the ",[67,178,179],{},"collection"," — you have to clearly say which collection it is. For example, say I want to add a record to the Users collection:",[17,182,183],{},[164,184],{"alt":179,"src":185},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-01-22%2022.29.37.png",[17,187,188,189,192,193,196],{},"So to add a user to the users collection, you'd write ",[67,190,191],{},"db.users.insertOne"," or ",[67,194,195],{},"db.users.insertMany",".",[17,198,199,200,203,204,196],{},"That diagram also tells us something else: if you wanted to add data to the ",[67,201,202],{},"news"," collection instead, it'd be ",[67,205,206],{},"db.news.insertOne",[17,208,209,210,212,213,196],{},"With that out of the way, let's circle back to our two bits of syntax: ",[67,211,120],{}," and ",[67,214,125],{},[17,216,217,218,212,220,223],{},"So what's the difference between ",[67,219,130],{},[67,221,222],{},"insertMany","? In short, one only adds a single record at a time, and the other lets you add a batch.",[17,225,226,227,230],{},"Let's start with the single insert and drop one user into the ",[67,228,229],{},"users"," collection:",[76,232,234],{"className":137,"code":233,"language":139,"meta":81,"style":81},"db.users.insertOne({\n  \"name\": \"Ray\",\n  \"age\": 28,\n  \"status\": false\n})\n",[67,235,236,245,260,273,284],{"__ignoreMap":81},[85,237,238,240,242],{"class":87,"line":88},[85,239,147],{"class":146},[85,241,130],{"class":150},[85,243,244],{"class":146},"({\n",[85,246,247,251,254,257],{"class":87,"line":94},[85,248,250],{"class":249},"sTRMh","  \"name\"",[85,252,253],{"class":146},": ",[85,255,256],{"class":249},"\"Ray\"",[85,258,259],{"class":146},",\n",[85,261,262,265,267,271],{"class":87,"line":100},[85,263,264],{"class":249},"  \"age\"",[85,266,253],{"class":146},[85,268,270],{"class":269},"sCcAr","28",[85,272,259],{"class":146},[85,274,276,279,281],{"class":87,"line":275},4,[85,277,278],{"class":249},"  \"status\"",[85,280,253],{"class":146},[85,282,283],{"class":269},"false\n",[85,285,287],{"class":87,"line":286},5,[85,288,289],{"class":146},"})\n",[17,291,292],{},"Once you hit enter, if the insert worked, MongoDB sends back a message telling you it succeeded along with the new document ID:",[17,294,295],{},[164,296],{"alt":297,"src":298},"insertOne result","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-01-22%2022.59.20.png",[76,300,302],{"className":137,"code":301,"language":139,"meta":81,"style":81},"{\n  \"acknowledged\" : true,\n  \"insertedId\" : ObjectId(\"61ec1b832fecb74092ce1462\")\n}\n",[67,303,304,309,322,341],{"__ignoreMap":81},[85,305,306],{"class":87,"line":88},[85,307,308],{"class":146},"{\n",[85,310,311,314,317,320],{"class":87,"line":94},[85,312,313],{"class":249},"  \"acknowledged\"",[85,315,316],{"class":146}," : ",[85,318,319],{"class":269},"true",[85,321,259],{"class":146},[85,323,324,327,329,332,335,338],{"class":87,"line":100},[85,325,326],{"class":249},"  \"insertedId\"",[85,328,316],{"class":146},[85,330,331],{"class":150},"ObjectId",[85,333,334],{"class":146},"(",[85,336,337],{"class":249},"\"61ec1b832fecb74092ce1462\"",[85,339,340],{"class":146},")\n",[85,342,343],{"class":87,"line":275},[85,344,345],{"class":146},"}\n",[17,347,348,349,351],{},"If you want to add multiple records at once, use ",[67,350,222],{}," — and it takes an array of objects:",[76,353,355],{"className":137,"code":354,"language":139,"meta":81,"style":81},"db.users.insertMany([\n  {\n    \"name\": \"Jack\",\n    \"age\": 25,\n    \"status\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"Roy\",\n    \"age\": 25,\n    \"status\": false\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"Mark\",\n    \"age\": 25,\n    \"status\": false\n  },\n])\n",[67,356,357,366,371,383,395,404,410,415,427,438,447,452,457,469,480,489,494],{"__ignoreMap":81},[85,358,359,361,363],{"class":87,"line":88},[85,360,147],{"class":146},[85,362,222],{"class":150},[85,364,365],{"class":146},"([\n",[85,367,368],{"class":87,"line":94},[85,369,370],{"class":146},"  {\n",[85,372,373,376,378,381],{"class":87,"line":100},[85,374,375],{"class":249},"    \"name\"",[85,377,253],{"class":146},[85,379,380],{"class":249},"\"Jack\"",[85,382,259],{"class":146},[85,384,385,388,390,393],{"class":87,"line":275},[85,386,387],{"class":249},"    \"age\"",[85,389,253],{"class":146},[85,391,392],{"class":269},"25",[85,394,259],{"class":146},[85,396,397,400,402],{"class":87,"line":286},[85,398,399],{"class":249},"    \"status\"",[85,401,253],{"class":146},[85,403,283],{"class":269},[85,405,407],{"class":87,"line":406},6,[85,408,409],{"class":146},"  },\n",[85,411,413],{"class":87,"line":412},7,[85,414,370],{"class":146},[85,416,418,420,422,425],{"class":87,"line":417},8,[85,419,375],{"class":249},[85,421,253],{"class":146},[85,423,424],{"class":249},"\"Roy\"",[85,426,259],{"class":146},[85,428,430,432,434,436],{"class":87,"line":429},9,[85,431,387],{"class":249},[85,433,253],{"class":146},[85,435,392],{"class":269},[85,437,259],{"class":146},[85,439,441,443,445],{"class":87,"line":440},10,[85,442,399],{"class":249},[85,444,253],{"class":146},[85,446,283],{"class":269},[85,448,450],{"class":87,"line":449},11,[85,451,409],{"class":146},[85,453,455],{"class":87,"line":454},12,[85,456,370],{"class":146},[85,458,460,462,464,467],{"class":87,"line":459},13,[85,461,375],{"class":249},[85,463,253],{"class":146},[85,465,466],{"class":249},"\"Mark\"",[85,468,259],{"class":146},[85,470,472,474,476,478],{"class":87,"line":471},14,[85,473,387],{"class":249},[85,475,253],{"class":146},[85,477,392],{"class":269},[85,479,259],{"class":146},[85,481,483,485,487],{"class":87,"line":482},15,[85,484,399],{"class":249},[85,486,253],{"class":146},[85,488,283],{"class":269},[85,490,492],{"class":87,"line":491},16,[85,493,409],{"class":146},[85,495,497],{"class":87,"line":496},17,[85,498,499],{"class":146},"])\n",[17,501,502,503,506],{},"When it succeeds, MongoDB sends back a result again, but you'll notice ",[67,504,505],{},"insertedIds"," is now an array:",[17,508,509],{},[164,510],{"alt":511,"src":512},"insertMany result","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-01-22%2023.05.32.png",[76,514,516],{"className":137,"code":515,"language":139,"meta":81,"style":81},"{\n  \"acknowledged\" : true,\n  \"insertedIds\" : [\n    ObjectId(\"61ec1cf32fecb74092ce1463\"),\n    ObjectId(\"61ec1cf32fecb74092ce1464\"),\n    ObjectId(\"61ec1cf32fecb74092ce1465\")\n  ]\n}\n",[67,517,518,522,532,540,553,564,575,580],{"__ignoreMap":81},[85,519,520],{"class":87,"line":88},[85,521,308],{"class":146},[85,523,524,526,528,530],{"class":87,"line":94},[85,525,313],{"class":249},[85,527,316],{"class":146},[85,529,319],{"class":269},[85,531,259],{"class":146},[85,533,534,537],{"class":87,"line":100},[85,535,536],{"class":249},"  \"insertedIds\"",[85,538,539],{"class":146}," : [\n",[85,541,542,545,547,550],{"class":87,"line":275},[85,543,544],{"class":150},"    ObjectId",[85,546,334],{"class":146},[85,548,549],{"class":249},"\"61ec1cf32fecb74092ce1463\"",[85,551,552],{"class":146},"),\n",[85,554,555,557,559,562],{"class":87,"line":286},[85,556,544],{"class":150},[85,558,334],{"class":146},[85,560,561],{"class":249},"\"61ec1cf32fecb74092ce1464\"",[85,563,552],{"class":146},[85,565,566,568,570,573],{"class":87,"line":406},[85,567,544],{"class":150},[85,569,334],{"class":146},[85,571,572],{"class":249},"\"61ec1cf32fecb74092ce1465\"",[85,574,340],{"class":146},[85,576,577],{"class":87,"line":412},[85,578,579],{"class":146},"  ]\n",[85,581,582],{"class":87,"line":417},[85,583,345],{"class":146},[17,585,586],{},"So now the data is all sitting inside the users collection. Each of these records is called a document, and in MongoDB the property and its value are Field: value. If that's hard to remember, just think of it like an object's Key: value:",[17,588,589],{},[164,590],{"alt":591,"src":592},"MongoDB structure","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-01-22%2023.10.49.png",[17,594,595],{},"And that's the overall MongoDB structure.\n\n",[597,598,599],"style",{},"html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sj_SG, html code.shiki .sj_SG{--shiki-default:#DBB7FF}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}html pre.shiki code .sCcAr, html code.shiki .sCcAr{--shiki-default:#91CBFF}",{"title":81,"searchDepth":94,"depth":94,"links":601},[602,603,604],{"id":14,"depth":94,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":94,"text":23},{"id":106,"depth":94,"text":107},"Nodejs","2022-02-15 08:55:19","Now that we've gotten comfortable with the basic MongoDB operations, the next obvious step is CRUD. We're still going to be poking around in the terminal, so fire it up and let's get into the Create part — insertOne and insertMany.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002Fforced-to-eat-mango-frontend-03-mongodb-crud-create","3",{"title":6,"description":607},false,"en\u002FNodejs\u002Fforced-to-eat-mango-frontend-03-mongodb-crud-create",[618,619,620],"MongoDB","Node.js","Forced to Eat Mango as a Frontend Engineer",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F15\u002Fforced-to-eat-mango-frontend-03-mongodb-crud-create\u002F","JJPuqkH87iBZtmINJPldqhFqazrK2wQ8P-OyS6l2Zpc",{"newer":625,"older":629},{"url":626,"title":627,"date":628},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F16\u002Fforced-to-eat-mango-frontend-04-mongodb-crud-read\u002F","(4) The Frontend Dev Forced to Eat Mango - MongoDB CRUD: Read","2022-02-16 08:15:35",{"url":630,"title":631,"date":632},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F14\u002Fmango-frontend-02-mongodb-basics\u002F","Forced to Eat Mango (2): MongoDB Basics in the Terminal","2022-02-14 15:01:45",[634,639,644],{"url":635,"title":636,"date":637,"readingMinutes":638},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2026\u002F01\u002F13\u002Frun-multiple-commands-with-concurrently\u002F","Tired of Opening Multiple Terminals to Run Commands? Use Concurrently","2026-01-13 09:45:28","2",{"url":640,"title":641,"date":642,"readingMinutes":643},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2025\u002F03\u002F13\u002Fhexschool-ecommerce-api-complete-tutorial\u002F","Hexschool Capstone Class Study Group: Complete E-commerce API Tutorial","2025-03-13 09:13:26","9",{"url":645,"title":646,"date":647,"readingMinutes":648},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2024\u002F12\u002F25\u002Fpm2-process-manager-not-pm25\u002F","PM2 Is Process Manager, Not PM2.5","2024-12-25 10:31:33","5",1784011707293]